4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, a person desiring to engage
6 in the practice of general contracting must be licensed
7 by the Alabama Board of General Contractors before
8 operating as a general contractor.
9 Also under existing law, various types of work
10 and other services are exempt from the requirements to
11 be licensed as a general contractor.
12 This bill would add to the list of exemptions
13 from the general contractor law the following: Painting
14 services, janitorial services, waxing floor services,
15 pressure washing services, maintenance of security
16 systems, lighting and filter replacement services, and
17 maintenance of existing plumbing, air conditioning, and
18 electrical systems.
19
20
21 A BILL
22 TO BE ENTITLED
23 AN ACT
24
25 Relating to general contracting; to amend Section
26 34-8-7, Code of Alabama 1975, to provide additional services
27 to the list of exemptions to the requirements of the general
28 contracting law.
