29 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
30 Section 1. Section 34-8-7, Code of Alabama 1975, is
31 amended to read as follows:
32 "§34-8-7
33 (a) The following shall be exempted from this chapter:
34 (1) The practice of general contracting, as defined in
35 Section 34-8-1, by an authorized representative of the United
36 States Government, the State of Alabama, or an incorporated
37 town, city, or county in this state, which is under the
38 supervision of a licensed architect or engineer, provided any
39 work contracted out by the authorized representative shall
40 comply with the definition in this chapter for general
41 contractor.
42 (2) The construction of any residence or private
43 dwelling.
44 (3) A person, firm, or corporation constructing a
45 building or other improvements on his, her, or its own
46 property, provided that any of the work contracted out
47 complies with the definition in this chapter for general
48 contractor. A municipal governing body or municipal regulatory
49 body may not enact any ordinance or law restricting or
50 altering this exemption. Any municipal ordinance or regulation
51 that conflicts with this exemption is repealed effective June
52 11, 2015.
53 (4) The installation, repair, maintenance, or removal
54 of facilities, equipment, or systems used in or substantially
55 related to the generation, transmission, or distribution of
56 electric power, natural gas, or telecommunications in an
Page 2

