85 (7) Routine landscape maintenance work that includes
86 cutting grass; trimming, replacing, and removal of bushes,
87 shrubs, and similar items; the placement and removal of pine
88 straw, mulch, bark, and similar ground covers; and other
89 routine ground maintenance.
90 (8) The provision of temporary labor by a labor broker
91 or other temporary labor provider that provides workers to a
92 general contractor to perform work under the supervision and
93 control of that general contractor. For the purposes of
94 licensing, temporary workers are deemed to fall under the
95 license of the general contractor to whom they are provided.
96 This exemption does not allow labor brokers or other temporary
97 labor providers to act as subcontractors or to assume a scope
98 of work for a project as a subcontractor.
99 (9) Painting services.
100 (10) Cleaning, waste disposal, and janitorial services.
101 (11) Stripping and waxing floor services.
102 (12) Pressure washing services.
103 (13) Maintenance of existing security and access
104 control systems.
105 (14) Lighting and filter replacement services.
106 (15) Maintenance of existing plumbing, air
107 conditioning, and electrical systems.
108 (b) The exemptions provided in subsection (a) shall
109 exclude a swimming pool contractor. Provided, however, a
110 person, firm, or corporation constructing a swimming pool on
111 his, her, or its the person's own property shall be exempted
