113 (c) A subcontractor, as defined in Section 34-8-1(c),
114 is subject to and shall comply with this chapter as specified
115 for a general contractor except as follows:
116 (1) A subcontractor shall pay one-half of the fees
117 required in this chapter for a general contractor.
118 (2) No bid limits shall be established for a
119 subcontractor.
120 (3) A subcontractor shall submit with license
121 application and renewals a statement of financial condition as
122 prescribed by the board.
123 (4) A subcontractor shall furnish three references from
124 any combination of the following: Licensed general
125 contractors, registered professional engineers, or registered
126 architects, or qualified person, as declared by the board, for
127 whom they have worked. If a subcontractor has only been
128 employed by one company, the subcontractor shall provide the
129 following: Three or more jobs he or she has worked on, the
130 amounts of the contracts, the time period of the contracts,
131 the location of the contracts, and a statement of experience.
132 (5) A subcontractor is not required to be licensed at
133 the time a project is bid, but must be licensed with the board
134 prior to beginning work on the project.
135 (6) A general contractor license and license number
136 issued by the board to subcontractors shall denote
137 subcontractor status.
138 (7) A subcontractor is not required to sit for any
139 examination before being licensed."
